{
  "id": "019d2da6-b2ef-7ae2-ba3f-7d9e8e47268b",
  "content": "## Index Coverage & Staleness Detection — Implementation Complete\n\n### What\nAdded `index_coverage`, `index_stale`, and 5 supporting fields to `GET /api/dashboard/status`. New `POST /api/dashboard/status/refresh-coverage` endpoint for on-demand recomputation. Three-layer comparison: disk files vs Redb SCOPE_INDEX vs HNSW_TO_UUID.\n\n### Architecture\n- `IndexCoverageCache` uses `std::sync::Mutex` (not `tokio::sync::Mutex`) with brief lock holds — avoids complex handler futures with dual axum 0.7/0.8. Async `refresh()` does spawn_blocking for disk I/O.\n- Background loop in main.rs refreshes coverage every `coverage_ttl_secs` (default 60s). TTL is captured once at startup — hot-reload changes require restart despite `dashboard` being in HOT_RELOADABLE_SECTIONS.\n- `CoverageResponse` typed struct shared between status and refresh endpoints (eliminates untyped serde_json::Value divergence).\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- Coverage = hnsw_count / disk_count (not store_count). Clamped to 1.0 when orphaned entries exist.\n- `index_stale` uses strict less-than (`<`), not `<=` — coverage exactly at threshold is NOT stale.\n- `count_json_files` is flat (non-recursive) matching current knowledge file layout.\n- PostgresStore fallback: hnsw_count = store_count (pgvector manages its own index).\n\n### Review Findings (deferred for follow-up)\n- Nest 7 flat fields under `index_coverage` object (API breaking change)\n- Add `index_scope_id` field (multi-scope awareness)\n- Add remediation hints when stale\n- Add orphan detection convenience field\n- Rate-limit refresh endpoint",
  "source_version": "mcp",
